## Category Card Background тАФ Never Use `--theme-muted` for Card Fills

**Problem:** Using `bg-[var(--theme-muted)]` as the background for category cards makes them invisible. `--theme-muted` is typically white or off-white (the hero section background), and the card text is `text-white` тАФ producing white-on-white.

**Fix:** Use `bg-[var(--theme-primary)]` (the accent/action color) for category card backgrounds. It's always a visible, contrasting color that the theme author has already chosen for buttons.

```json
// тЭМ BAD тАФ hero-bg is white/off-white; card is invisible
{ "type": "Box", "props": { "className": "... bg-[var(--theme-muted)]" },
  "children": [{ "type": "Text", "props": { "className": "text-white" }, "text": "Women" }] }

// тЬЕ GOOD тАФ shop-button is always a visible accent color
{ "type": "Box", "props": { "className": "... bg-[var(--theme-primary)] hover:opacity-80" },
  "children": [{ "type": "Text", "props": { "className": "text-[var(--theme-primary-foreground)]" }, "text": "{{$item.name}}" }] }
```

**Applies to:** Category grid cards, collection tiles, any solid-color card that needs a visible background.

