## forEach `listPath` vs `list` тАФ Use the Right Config Key

**Problem:** The `forEach` step in a workflow supports two list sources:
- `listPath` (or `itemsPath`): a variable UUID or state path to read the array from at runtime
- `list`: an inline hardcoded array of values

Confusing these (e.g. using `listPath` when you have an inline array, or missing both) causes the loop body to never execute.

**Fix:** Choose the right key based on your data source:

```json
// тЬЕ forEach over a runtime variable (UUID = array stored in variables.json)
{
  "id": "s-loop",
  "type": "forEach",
  "config": { "listPath": "wa000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000042" },
  "loopBody": [...]
}

// тЬЕ forEach over an inline literal array
{
  "id": "s-loop",
  "type": "forEach",
  "config": { "list": ["A", "B", "C"] },
  "loopBody": [...]
}
```

Inside the loop body, access the current item via:
- **Text templates:** `{{context.item.data.value}}`
- **Formula expressions:** `context?.item?.data?.value`

`context.item.data.value` is set to the raw array element; `context.item.data.index` is the 0-based iteration index.

**Applies to:** All `changeVariableValue` actions in `config/actions/`, all `variables['UUID']` conditions in screens and fragments.

---

## `setFormState` Step тАФ `isSubmitted` / `isSubmitting` Display

**How `setFormState` works:** The `setFormState` workflow step writes `isSubmitting`/`isSubmitted` directly to `local.data.form` in both the global variable store and the Zustand SDUI store.

**Display rule:** To display these flags in the UI, use `{{local.data.form.isSubmitted}}` / `{{local.data.form.isSubmitting}}` template syntax тАФ NOT `{ "expr": "String(local?.data?.form?.isSubmitted ?? false)" }`.

**Why:** `{ "expr": "..." }` text nodes use `extractPathsFromObject` for dependency tracking, which only extracts `{{...}}` patterns from expression strings. A raw JS expression like `String(local?.data?.form?.isSubmitted ?? false)` generates **zero subscriptions** тАФ the node never re-renders when the value changes. Template strings `{{path}}` do generate subscriptions via `extractPathsFromTemplate`.

```json
// тЭМ BAD тАФ no subscription generated; node never re-renders when isSubmitted changes
{ "type": "Text", "text": { "expr": "String(local?.data?.form?.isSubmitted ?? false)" } }

// тЬЕ GOOD тАФ generates subscription to local.data.form.isSubmitted; re-renders on change
{ "type": "Text", "text": "{{local.data.form.isSubmitted}}" }
```

**`setFormState` step lifecycle pattern (submit workflow):**

```json
"waFormSubmit": {
  "trigger": "submit",
  "steps": [
    { "id": "s1", "type": "setFormState", "config": { "isSubmitting": true } },
    { "id": "s2", "type": "changeVariableValue", "config": { "variableName": "UUID-result", "value": { "formula": "..." } } },
    { "id": "s3", "type": "changeVariableValue", "config": { "variableName": "UUID-validationError", "value": "" } },
    { "id": "s4", "type": "setFormState", "config": { "isSubmitting": false, "isSubmitted": true } }
  ]
}
```

**`resetForm` auto-clears these:** `resetFormHandler` sets `isSubmitting: false` and `isSubmitted: false` as part of the empty form state тАФ no extra `setFormState` step needed in the reset workflow.

**FormContainer sync `useEffect` тАФ preserve workflow writes:** The `useEffect` that syncs `formState` back to the global store is patched to preserve `isSubmitting`/`isSubmitted` from the store when not resetting. This prevents the React state snapshot (which is stale at `useEffect` fire time) from overwriting values set by `setFormState` workflow steps running concurrently as microtasks.

**Rule:** Always use `{{local.data.form.isSubmitted}}` and `{{local.data.form.isSubmitting}}` in display nodes. Never use `expr` for these тАФ you'll get a node that shows the initial render value forever.

---

## `updateCollection` тАФ In-Memory Data Manipulation

`updateCollection` with `updateType: "insert"`, `"update"`, or `"delete"` performs **in-memory mutations** on the Zustand store тАФ it does NOT make an API call.

### Storage key rule тАФ always use `.data` sub-path

**Problem:** Storing the array directly at `collections.UUID` (i.e. `ctx.setData("collections.UUID", [...])`) causes `setNestedValue` to overwrite it with `{loading: false}` when it processes the sibling path `collections.UUID.loading`. In `setNestedValue`, when an intermediate path segment holds an array, the traversal code falls back to `{}` (since arrays fail the `!Array.isArray(next)` guard), silently replacing the array.

**Fix (built into the engine):** `refetchDataSourceHandler` always stores the array at `collections.UUID.data` (i.e. the flat Zustand key `"collections.UUID.data"`). The `updateType` config uses `dataPath: "data"` by default. Sibling `.loading` and `.error` keys then safely modify the wrapping object without destroying the array.

```json
// тЬЕ CORRECT тАФ in-memory updateCollection workflow
{
  "type": "updateCollection",
  "config": {
    "collectionId": "UUID",
    "updateType": "insert",
    "position": 0,
    "data": "{\"id\":\"new-1\",\"name\":\"New Item\"}"
  }
}
```

**Supported updateTypes:**

| `updateType` | Effect | Required config |
|---|---|---|
| `"replaceAll"` + `data` | Replaces the stored array with `data` (parsed from JSON string or formula) | `data` |
| `"replaceAll"` (no `data`) | Triggers a real API refetch | тАФ |
| `"insert"` | Inserts item at `position` (default: end) | `data`, optional `position` |
| `"update"` | Finds item by `findBy: "id"` + `idKey` + `idValue`, merges when `merge: true` | `data`, `findBy`, `idKey`, `idValue` |
| `"delete"` | Removes item found by `findBy: "id"` + `idKey` + `idValue` | `findBy`, `idKey`, `idValue` |

**Accessing the array after mutation:** the array lives at `collections.UUID.data`, NOT `collections.UUID`:

```json
// Map over in-memory items
"map": "collections.c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-123456789012.data"

// Count тАФ use template syntax (see subscription rule below)
"text": "{{collections.c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-123456789012.data.length}}"
```

---

## Reactive Subscriptions тАФ `text: { expr }` and `condition` Strings Are NOT Subscribed

**Problem:** Each renderer node subscribes only to the paths returned by `extractNodeDependencies`. This extractor finds paths inside `{{...}}` template strings only. Plain formula strings in `text: { "expr": "..." }` or `"condition": "formula string"` have **no `{{...}}`**, so **zero deps are extracted** and the node **never re-renders** when store data changes.

The `map` field with a string path IS correctly subscribed.

**Fix тАФ use the right syntax per field:**

| Field | Wrong (not subscribed) | Correct (subscribed) |
|---|---|---|
| `text` count/length | `"text": { "expr": "arr.length" }` | `"text": "{{path.to.array.length}}"` |
| `text` formula result | `"text": { "expr": "x + y" }` | Use `{{path}}` template or move to computed |
| `condition` (needs own subscription) | `"condition": "path.length === 0"` | pair with a `text: "{{path.length}}"` on the same node, OR use a parent `map` that already subscribes |

```json
// тЭМ BAD тАФ shows 0 forever; never re-renders when collection.data changes
{ "text": { "expr": "(collections['UUID']?.data || []).length", "suffix": "" } }

// тЬЕ GOOD тАФ subscribed; updates immediately when data changes
{ "text": "{{collections.UUID.data.length}}" }
```

**`condition` subscription rule:** Formula string conditions evaluate correctly at runtime but do NOT self-subscribe. A condition node re-renders (and re-evaluates its condition) whenever ANY other subscribed path on that node changes:
- If the node has `"text": "{{path}}"` on the same path the condition checks тЖТ re-renders correctly тЬУ
- If the node has no `text` or `props` subscriptions тЖТ condition is evaluated once on mount and never again тЬЧ

**Inline error text nodes use this correctly:**
```json
{
  "type": "Text",
  "condition": "local?.data?.form?.fields?.['fieldName']?.isValid",
  "props": { "className": "text-xs text-red-500" },
  "text": "{{local.data.form.fields['fieldName'].isValid}}"
}
```
The `text` template subscribes to `local.data.form.fields.fieldName.isValid`. When validation writes an error, the subscription fires, the node re-renders, and the `condition` is re-evaluated with the new error string (truthy тЖТ node shows). The same `{{path}}` subscription drives both display and visibility.

**тЪая╕П JSON Logic conditions (`{ "not": { "var": "..." } }`, `{ "==": [...] }`) are NOT supported and have been removed.** The `{ "var" }` branch was removed from `extractPathsFromObject` in `dependency-extractor.ts`. Never use JSON Logic syntax in `condition` тАФ it never evaluated correctly and is now unsupported for subscriptions too.

**`condition` subscription self-subscribes via formula string:** The renderer directly extracts paths from formula strings in `condition` values тАФ any `variables['UUID']`, `collections['UUID']`, `route.*`, or other paths in the formula string generate subscriptions automatically.

```json
// тЭМ WRONG тАФ JSON Logic; removed from codebase
{ "condition": { "not": { "var": "collections.UUID.data.length" } } }

// тЬЕ CORRECT тАФ formula string; auto-subscribes and evaluates correctly
{ "condition": "!collections?.['c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-123456789012']?.data?.length" }
{ "condition": "!local?.data?.form?.isSubmitting" }
{ "condition": "variables?.['UUID'] === 'active'" }
```

**Rule:** For any node that displays or gates on dynamically-changing store data:
- Use `{{path}}` template strings for `text` (subscribed)
- Use **plain JS formula strings** for `condition` (self-subscribing via `extractPathsFromObject` scanning for identifiers)
- Only use `text: { "expr": "..." }` for static/config-time values or inside a `map` scope where the parent already re-renders

