## Animated Node `animNodeOwnsId` тАФ Outer Wrapper Style Rule

**Problem:** In builder mode, when a node has an animation config, `animNodeOwnsId` is true and the renderer wraps the element in an `AnimatedNode`. The outer animated wrapper is the selectable/resizable target. A previous bug spread the full `cleanProps.style` (which = `arbStyles` + `node.props.style`) to `outerStyle`, then deleted it from the inner element. This caused:
- Padding that existed in both arbStyles AND compiled CSS classes to be applied twice (outer padding + inner CSS padding), making builder elements taller/wider than preview.
- Non-JIT-compiled arbitrary classes to lose their inline style fallback on the inner element.

**Fix (applied in `lib/sdui/renderer.tsx` `animNodeOwnsId` block):**
- `outerFromArb` тАФ only keys in `OUTER_PASSTHROUGH` (`width`, `height`, size constraints, `top`/`right`/`bottom`/`left`, `borderRadius` variants, `zIndex`) from `arbStyles` go to the outer wrapper.
- `nodePropsStyle` тАФ only `node.props.style` (explicit JSON style written by tools like `set_opacity`) goes to the outer wrapper, NOT the full `cleanProps.style`.
- `cleanProps.style` is **not deleted** тАФ the inner element keeps its full arbStyles inline styles so non-compiled arbitrary classes still render.

```ts
// тЬЕ CORRECT
const outerFromArb: Record<string, unknown> = {};
for (const key of OUTER_PASSTHROUGH) {
  if (key in arbStyles) outerFromArb[key] = arbStyles[key];
}
const nodePropsStyle = (node.props?.style ?? {}) as Record<string, unknown>;
const styleForOuter = { ...outerFromArb, ...nodePropsStyle };
// Do NOT delete cleanProps.style

// тЭМ WRONG тАФ caused double padding and lost inline styles
const innerStyle = cleanProps.style; // includes arbStyles padding!
const styleForOuter = { ...outerFromArb, ...innerStyle }; // padding leaks to outer
delete cleanProps.style; // inner loses inline style fallback
```

**Rule:** When modifying the `animNodeOwnsId` block in `renderer.tsx`, never spread the full `cleanProps.style` into `outerStyle` and never delete `cleanProps.style` from the inner element.

---

## Percentage Widths on Animated Nodes (Builder Mode) тАФ Use `flex-1` or Explicit `px`/`vh` Instead

**Problem:** In builder mode, a node with `w-[45%]` AND an animation config (enter, hover, loop, etc.) renders its image too small. The outer `Animated.View` wrapper gets `width: '45%'` correctly (45% of grandparent), but the inner element also keeps `width: '45%'` (45% of the outer = ~20% of grandparent). An `Image` child with `w-full h-full` then fills that already-shrunken inner box = too small.

**Root cause:** The `animNodeOwnsId` inner-fill logic in `renderer.tsx` previously only replaced **number** widths with `'100%'` (e.g. `480` from `w-[480px]`). String percentage widths like `'45%'` (produced by `classToInlineStyle('w-[45%]')`) were not replaced, so the inner element kept `width: '45%'` of the outer wrapper.

**Fix (applied in `lib/sdui/renderer.tsx`):** Extended the `animNodeOwnsId` width/height replacement to cover all non-intrinsic values (including string percentages):

```ts
// Before тАФ only numbers were replaced; '45%' was left as-is on the inner
if ('width' in innerStyles && typeof innerStyles.width === 'number') innerStyles.width = '100%';

// After тАФ numbers AND percentage strings are replaced; only intrinsic keywords ('fit-content', 'auto') are preserved
const INTRINSIC_KW_INNER = ['fit-content', 'max-content', 'min-content', 'auto'];
if ('width'  in innerStyles && !INTRINSIC_KW_INNER.includes(String(innerStyles.width  ?? ''))) innerStyles.width  = '100%';
if ('height' in innerStyles && !INTRINSIC_KW_INNER.includes(String(innerStyles.height ?? ''))) innerStyles.height = '100%';
```

**Note:** This bug only manifests in builder mode (`animNodeOwnsId = true`). In preview mode, the `useSingleElementPath` renders the animated node as a single element (no outer wrapper), so `w-[45%]` is applied correctly to the element itself.

**Applies to:** Any animated node (with enter, hover, loop, press, etc.) in the visual builder that uses a percentage-based width or height class like `w-[45%]`, `h-[60%]`, `w-[33%]`, etc.

---

## Background Media тАФ No Default Border-Radius (Changed)

`Image` and `Video` components no longer ship with a default `rounded-[6px]`. There is no cleanup step needed when using them as background layers.

Use `set_border(id, {radius: N})` only when you explicitly want rounded corners on an inline image or video тАФ it is never needed for background use.

## Layout Containers тАФ Minimal Defaults (Changed)

`Box`, `Row`, `VStack`, `HStack`, `Center`, and `Grid` ship with only identity classes (flex direction, alignment). No `w-full`, no `gap-*`, no `grid-cols-*`. The AI sets width, gap, and grid columns explicitly via tools (`set_size`, `set_spacing`, `set_layout`).

- `Box`: `flex flex-col`
- `Row`: `flex flex-row items-center`
- `VStack`: `flex flex-col`
- `HStack`: `flex flex-row items-center`
- `Center`: `flex flex-col items-center justify-center`
- `Grid`: `grid`

CSS flexbox `align-items: stretch` (the default) makes children fill parent width automatically тАФ `w-full` is not needed and was removed because it broke centering in `items-center` parents.

If a container picks up unwanted spacing, it is coming from a component that intentionally has padding (e.g. `Card`, `Alert`) тАФ not from a generic layout container.

---

## Image Nodes тАФ Always Wrap in a Box When Using Position or Percentage Sizes

**Problem:** Placing an `Image` node as a direct absolutely-positioned child of a flex container (e.g. `flex: 0.55`) causes the image to collapse to zero or render at its natural media size. `<img>` cannot act as a CSS containing block, and percentage `width`/`height` on a `position: absolute` child require an explicit CSS `width` (or `height`) on the containing block. A flex item sized only via `flex: 0.55` has no explicit CSS `width`, so the browser cannot resolve the percentage.

**Fix:** Always wrap `Image` nodes in a `Box` clip-wrapper for any collage, split-hero, layered, or positioned layout:

```
// тЬЕ CORRECT тАФ Box provides containing block; Image fills it 100%
gallery-container
  Box (clip-wrapper, height: "55vh", width: "420px", overflow: "hidden")
    Image (width: "100%", height: "100%", objectFit: "cover")

// тЭМ WRONG тАФ <img> cannot resolve percentage sizes inside a flex item
gallery-container (display: flex)
  Image (position: "absolute", width: "100%", height: "80%")
```

**Sizing rules for this pattern:**
- **Wrapper Box**: Use explicit **px or vh values** (e.g. `height: "55vh"`, `width: "420px"`). Never percentage dimensions on an absolutely-positioned Box inside a flex container.
- **Image inside wrapper**: Set `width: "100%"` and `height: "100%"` only тАФ no position, no explicit px sizing.

**Applies to:** Any layout where images sit inside collage grids, split-hero panels, layered sections, or any container whose CSS width is determined by flex/grid layout rather than an explicit pixel value.

---

## Absolutely-Positioned Animated Box тАФ Image/Children Render Outside Card (Builder Mode)

**Problem:** A `Box` with `className: "... absolute top-[50%] right-[60px] overflow-hidden ..."` and an animation (`loop`, `enter`, etc.) causes its children (e.g. `Image` with `w-full h-full`) to render outside the card boundaries in **builder mode**.

**Root cause:** In builder mode, `AnimatedNode` wraps the inner Box in an outer `Animated.View`. The renderer copies all `arbStyles` (including `position: absolute`, `top: 50%`, `right: 60px`, `zIndex: 20`) into `innerStyles`. Only `width`/`height` were replaced with `100%`. The remaining positioning properties cause the inner Box to be positioned at `top: 50%; right: 60px` **relative to the outer 500├Ч500 wrapper** тАФ placing it 250px from the top AND shifted outside the right boundary.

Additionally, `translateY: "-50%"` from `node.props.style` is composed into `transform: translateY(-50%)` on the inner element, further shifting it outside the outer.

**Fix (applied in `lib/sdui/renderer.tsx`):**
1. Strip `position`, `top`, `right`, `bottom`, `left`, `zIndex` from `innerStyles` when `animNodeOwnsId` is true.
2. Strip corresponding Tailwind class tokens (`absolute`, `top-[...]`, `right-[...]`, etc.) from `cleanProps.className` so NativeWind's compiled CSS doesn't re-apply them.
3. Strip `transform` from `cleanProps.style` тАФ `translateX/Y` from `node.props.style` are outer positioning transforms already forwarded to the outer Animated.View via `nodePropsStyle тЖТ outerStyle`.

The inner element becomes a clean `width: 100%; height: 100%` filler with no positioning. All positioning lives on the outer Animated.View wrapper.

**Rule:** Any absolutely-positioned Box with an animation config is safe тАФ the engine handles the stripping automatically. Just use `overflow-hidden` on the Box's className and the image clipping will work correctly.

---

## Centering with `translateX(-50%) translateY(-50%)` тАФ Broken in Preview Mode

**Problem:** An absolutely-positioned content overlay centered with the classic CSS trick:
```json
"style": { "translateX": "-50%", "translateY": "-50%" },
"className": "absolute top-[50%] left-[50%]"
```
тАжworks correctly in the **builder** but text appears off-center in **preview**.

**Root cause:** In preview mode, `useSingleElementPath=true` wraps the `Box` as `AnimatedComponent(Box)` via NativeWind's `cssInterop`. When Reanimated applies `animatedStyle` (which contains the static `translateX(-50%)` as a parsed transform) to a NativeWind-processed component, NativeWind's style pipeline doesn't reliably merge Reanimated's percentage transform string тАФ the centering shift is dropped. In builder mode, the outer `Animated.View` wrapper carries both `top/left` positioning and the transform as Reanimated-owned properties, bypassing NativeWind entirely, so it works.

**Fix (code тАФ already applied in `lib/sdui/renderer.tsx`):** When a node's `style` contains ANY `translateX`, `translateY`, or non-empty CSS `transform` string (e.g. `"rotate(-8deg)"`, `"translateX(-50%)"`, `"scale(1.1)"`), `_hasStaticStyleTransform` is set to `true`. This:
1. Forces `useSingleElementPath = false` тАФ the wrapper path is used instead of `AnimatedComponent(Box)`.
2. Sets `_willOwn = true` тАФ position/inset Tailwind tokens (`absolute`, `top-[...]`, `left-[...]`, `z-[...]`) are stripped from the inner `cleanProps.className`.
3. Those stripped values are forwarded to `outerStyle` via `sizeOverride` so the outer `Animated.View` carries `position: absolute; top: 50%; left: 50%`.
4. `staticTransform = "translateX(-50%) translateY(-50%)"` is composed into `animatedStyle` by the Reanimated worklet and applied to the raw outer `Animated.View` (no NativeWind interference) тАФ centering works in both preview and builder.

Both patterns now work correctly:

```json
// тЬЕ Classic CSS centering тАФ now works in preview too
{
  "style": { "translateX": "-50%", "translateY": "-50%" },
  "className": "items-center absolute z-[20] top-[50%] left-[50%]"
}

// тЬЕ Alternative тАФ inset-0 + flexbox (simpler, no transform needed)
{
  "className": "flex flex-col items-center justify-center absolute inset-0 z-[20]"
}
```

**When to use which:**
- `translateX(-50%)` centering: use when you need the container to have a fixed/max-width that doesn't fill the parent (e.g. `max-w-[900px]`). The container starts at `left:50%` and shifts left by half its own width.
- `inset-0 justify-center`: use when the container can fill the full parent and flexbox centers the children. Simpler and requires no `staticTransform` at all.

**Also:** add `text-center` to headline/subheadline Text nodes when centering тАФ `items-center` on the parent Box centers the text blocks but doesn't center text *within* each block.

